    • Constructor Detail

      • SpreadIndexVector

        public SpreadIndexVector(double fineFuelMoisture,
                         double adjustedFuelMoisture,
                         double dryingFactor,
                         double buildUpIndex,
                         double fineFuelSpread,
                         double timberSpreadIndex,
                         double fireLoadIndex)
        Instantiates a new spread index vector.
        Parameters:
        fineFuelMoisture - represents the moisture content of litter (forest material that can burn) measured in %
        adjustedFuelMoisture - fine fuel moisture adjusted for precipitation in the last day
        dryingFactor - ranges between 1 an 7 (inversely proportional to ffm)
        buildUpIndex - reflecting the combined cumulative effects of daily drying and precipitation in fuels (such as dead vegetation) with a 10 day time lag constant.
        fineFuelSpread - fire spread danger for grass fuel environments (measured in %)
        timberSpreadIndex - fire spread danger in environments with timber fuel (forests, measured in %)
        fireLoadIndex - rating of the maximum effort required to contain all probable fires
